{"name": "pulp2mat", "metadata": {"name": "pulp2mat", "version": "0.1.4", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Mathematics", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "pulp", "scipy"], "summary": "convert pulp model into matrix formulation for scipy.optimize.milp", "upload_time": 1732873028}, "documentation": ["# pulp2mat\n\nConvert pulp model into matrix formulation.\n\nIt can be easily thrown to scipy.optimize.milp function.\n\n\n# How to install\n\n```\n$ pip install pulp2mat\n```\n\nWithout poetry, please look at pyproject.toml and install all dependencies manually. \n\n# Quick Example\n\nFor example, the binpacking problem can be formulated with pulp as below;\n\n```python\nimport pulp as pl\nimport numpy as np\n\nitem_sizes = np.array([7, 3, 3, 1, 6, 8, 4, 9, 5, 2])\nnum_items = len(item_sizes)\nnum_bins = len(item_sizes)\nbin_size = 10\n\n# Variables * must be defined as dictionaries\nx = {\n    (i, j): pl.LpVariable(\"x_{}_{}\".format(i, j), cat=pl.LpBinary)\n    for i in range(num_items)\n    for j in range(num_bins)\n}\ny = {\n    j: pl.LpVariable(\"y_{}\".format(j), cat=pl.LpBinary)\n    for j in range(num_bins)\n}\n\nproblem = pl.LpProblem()\n\n# Bin size constraint for each bin\nfor j in range(num_bins):\n    problem += (\n        pl.lpSum(\n            x[i, j] * item_sizes[i] for i in range(num_items)\n        )\n        <= bin_size * y[j]\n    )\n# One-hot constraint for each item\nfor i in range(num_items):\n    problem += pl.lpSum(x[i, j] for j in range(num_bins)) == 1\n\n# Objective: minimize number of bins used.\nproblem += pl.lpSum(y[j] for j in range(num_bins))\n```\n\nthe ```pulp.LpProblem``` object and the list of variable dictionaries can be converted to the matrix format for ```scipy.optimize.milp```.\n\n```python\nimport pulp2mat\nfrom scipy.optimize import milp\nc, integrality, constraints, bounds = pulp2mat.convert_all(problem)\nresult = milp(c, integrality=integrality, constraints=constraints, bounds=bounds)\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pulp2mat", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pulp2mat.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pulp2mat.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pulp2mat.__license__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pulp2mat.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pulp2mat.__author_email__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pulp2mat.__url__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pulp2mat.lp2mat", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pulp2mat.lp2mat.get_vars", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "problem", "type": {"name": "pl.LpProblem", "xref": {"fqname": "pulp.LpProblem", "project": "pulp"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.float64", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.float64", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.float64", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.float64", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}]}]}, {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pulp2mat.lp2mat.get_constraint_matrix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "problem", "type": {"name": "pl.LpProblem", "xref": {"fqname": "pulp.LpProblem", "project": "pulp"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "vars_dict", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.float64", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.float64", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.float64", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.float64", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["get constraint matrix c and bound arrays b_l, b_u such that;\nb_l <= c.dot(x) <= b_u\n\nArgs:\n    problem (pl.LpProblem): pulp model to be converted\n    vars_dict (dict[str, Tuple[int, int, np.float64, np.float64]]): _description_\n\nReturns:\n    Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray, np.ndarray]: constraint matrix c, bound arrays b_l, b_u"]}, {"name": "pulp2mat.lp2mat.get_objective_array", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "problem", "type": {"name": "pl.LpProblem", "xref": {"fqname": "pulp.LpProbl